    ],
    "notes": "Detection should focus on netstat.exe (or equivalent: net-stat Fawkes command) spawned by a non-standard parent — specifically any parent executable residing under AppData, Temp, or other user-writable paths. The parent path C:\\Users\\*\\AppData\\Roaming\\* combined with a child process of netstat.exe, net.exe, or ipconfig.exe is a high-fidelity signal. Benign cases typically show cmd.exe, powershell.exe, or known monitoring agents (SolarWinds, SCCM, etc.) as parents. The accompanying outbound C2 beacon from the same PID post-enumeration is a strong corroborating signal for kill-chain correlation."
  },
